verses.roman:
prabhu kahe,--"eho haya, āge kaha āra"
rāya kahe,--"īhā va-i buddhi-gati nāhi āra"

synonyms: prabhu kahe—Lord Caitanya Mahāprabhu said; eho haya—this is all right; āge kaha āra—please go forward and say more; rāya kahe—Rāmānanda Rāya replied; ihā va-i—except this; buddhi-gati—movement of my intelligence; nāhi—there is not; āra—any more.
translation: Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu said, "This is all right, but please continue." At that time Rāya Rāmānanda replied, "I don't think my intelligence goes beyond this."
